To accelerate, press and hold the <color #FF7B1A>Move Forward</color> key.
Note that your chocobo's stamina will decrease more quickly when accelerating.
Be warned─chocobos pushed too hard will become <color #FF7B1A>lathered</color> and lose stamina even more quickly!
Next, practice steering your chocobo.
Scattered throughout the course are <color #FF7B1A>magicked panels</color> which bestow various effects when triggered.
Your chocobo gained a temporary burst of speed! However, be warned: not all panels bestow beneficial effects!
In addition to magicked panels, you may come across treasure coffers containing <color #FF7B1A>race items</color>.
Race items will be added to your hotbar automatically, and can be used to help yourself or hinder your opponents.

<?0x60>Welcome, ladies and gentlemen! Thank you for joining us for this drawing of the Jumbo Cactpot.
Now, without further ado, let us set the wheels in motion!
And the winning number for draw <value> is...\n<?0x50>!
Whether or not you hit the Cactpot today, just remember: there's always drawing number <value> to look forward to!
Here you can practice the basics of chocobo racing.
Continue to accelerate and observe the effects. Once your chocobo's stamina is completely depleted, your speed will drop, and you will no longer be able to accelerate.
To alleviate this condition, release the <color #FF7B1A>Move Forward</color> key and allow your chocobo to rest.
Press the <color #FF7B1A>Move Left</color> and <color #FF7B1A>Move Right</color> keys to steer your chocobo from one side of the course to the other.
To trigger a magicked panel, steer your chocobo towards it.
In addition to steering away from panels, you can also <color #FF7B1A>jump</color> to avoid them.
Some treasure coffers will be suspended in mid-air, so to obtain the race items within, you will need to jump.
This concludes the chocobo racing training course.
You may repeat this course at any time should you wish to review the fundamentals.
Ride well, and good luck!
First, tilt the left analog stick up, or press <icon:13> key to accelerate.
To alleviate this condition, stop accelerating and allow your chocobo to rest.
Tilt the left analog stick to the left and right to steer your chocobo from one side of the course to the other.
All race chocobos will carry their rider to the end of a course. However, only a skilled jockey can guide his steed to victory.

Triple Triad is played by placing cards on a three-by-three grid.\nThe player to act first is decided at random.
Now it's your turn!\nPlace a card in one of the empty spaces adjacent to my card.
See how my card changed color?\nThis means you have “captured” the card.
Try to capture and control more cards than your opponent!\nThe match will end when all spaces on the grid have been filled.
And the match is over! Whoever controls the most cards\nat the end of the game is the winner!
